# Feature-Sliced Design

Full reference: `docs/feature-sliced-design.md` (official `llms-full.txt`). Consult it for edge cases.

## Layers (top → bottom, import direction is downward only)

`app` → `pages` → `widgets` → `features` → `entities` → `shared`

A module may only import from layers strictly below it. Never import upward or sideways within the same layer.

## Structure

- Layer → slice → segment. Example: `features/auth/{ui,model,api,lib,config}`.
- Slices group code by business domain, not by technical role.
- `shared` and `app` have no slices (segments only).

## Public API (mandatory)

- Every slice exposes a single entry point via `index.ts`.
- Import slices through their public API, never reach into internal files.

```ts
// BAD
import { LoginForm } from "@/features/auth/ui/LoginForm";
// GOOD
import { LoginForm } from "@/features/auth";
```

## Isolation

- No cross-imports between slices on the same layer. If two slices need shared code, lift it to a lower layer (`entities` or `shared`).

## Note on this repo

This project (CVere) already uses a Next.js `src/app` + `src/features/<domain>` layout. Apply FSD principles (domain slices, public APIs, downward-only imports) within that existing structure; do not restructure folders unless asked.
